gender_identity_M.Description: To what degree the subject felt male

gender_identity_F.Description: To what degree the subject felt female

sexual_attraction_M.Description: To what degree the subject was attracted to males

sexual_attraction_F.Description: To what degree the subject was attracted to females

BMI.LongName: Body mass index (rounded to nearest integer

handedness.Description: Whether someone is left-handed, right-handed, or ambidextrous

background_SES.Description: Background socio-economic status (based on parents' income and educational level (range 2-6)

education_level.Description: Level of education (as defined by the Central Bureau van de Statistiek, CBS)

religious_upbringing.Description: Whether the subject was religious or not

religious_now.Description: Whether the subject is religious now

Levels.no: Not religious at the moment of testing
Levels.yes: Religious at the moment of testing

religious_importance.Description: How much religion plays a role in the subject's life

NEO_A.Description: Score on the Agreeableness scale of the NEO-FFI

NEO_C.Description: Score on the Conscientiousness scale of the NEO-FFI

NEO_E.Description: Score on the Extraversion scale of the NEO-FFI

NEO_N.Description: Score on the Neuroticism scale of the NEO-FFI

NEO_O.Description: Score on the Openness scale of the NEO-FFI

STAI_T.Description: Trait anxiety (from the state-trait anxiety inventory)

DWI_TR_run1.Description: Repetition Time (TR) for the first DWI scan (if this scan doesn't exist for a subject, it is coded 'n/a')

DWI_TR_run2.Description: Repetition Time (TR) for the second DWI scan (if this scan doesn't exist for a subject, it is coded 'n/a')

DWI_TR_run3.Description: Repetition Time (TR) for the third DWI scan (if this scan doesn't exist for a subject, it is coded 'n/a')

README:
The ID1000 dataset is part of the Amsterdam Open MRI Collection (AOMIC), a collection of multimodal (3T) MRI datasets including structural (T1-weighted), diffusion-weighted, and (resting-state and task-based) functional BOLD MRI data, as well as detailed demographics and psychometric variables from a large set of healthy participants.

This dataset contains both raw and preprocessed data (and other "derivatives"), which is available on [Openneuro](https://openneuro.org/datasets/ds003097).

The contents of this dataset are described in detail in [this preprint](https://www.biorxiv.org/content/10.1101/2020.06.16.155317v1). More general information about the AOMIC datasets, including instructions on how to download (parts of) it, check out the [AOMIC website](https://nilab-uva.github.io/AOMIC.github.io/).
